THIS IS IMPORTANT!! -- In my experience, Mud admins deal with characters having the ability to do phenominal amounts of damage by 'buffing up' the mobs HPs, resists, and generally making them more difficult to kill.  EVERY TIME they do this, wizards become less and less wanted because we are do a FINITE amount of damage.  That's the problem.  We need to do more because they're raising the damage that mobs can take.  They've provided the means for melees to handle it.  Now it's OUR turn.  I wish they'd fix us instead of patronizing us.  Those of us who have been waiting patiently were expecting them (naively I guess) to truly consider the implications of their actions.  Right now, I don't think we're even speaking the same language.<br>
