No MOB 56+ can be interrupted. They can only be mesmerized by Glamour of Kintaz, and a great many can't be mesmerized anyway. As such, a binding spell such as this becomes helpful.<br>
Unfortunately...it IS a raid spell. Unless someone wants to do a high level xp camp with gating, uninterruptable mobs (myconid adepts=) will they intelligently take a wizard over a druid as their evacuator, ever. <br>
Again, we have to use this enhancement as a stepping stone for higher desires and needs to fix the Wizard class.<br>
<br>
As a final note, MOBs that resist stuns will probably resist this spell as well. The only difference is those that are 56+ that don't resist...though there is always Glamour of Kintaz; an interrupt that can be used against CH too. =-)<br>
I hear Trakanon gates. That's 8khp restored and one hell of a ping pong. =P <br>
But he is STUNNABLE! It's feasible to have 3 paladins try to interrupt...<br>
Oh well, rambling on here.<br>
One last point:<br>
Verant keeps stating that our damage potential is balanced. We did and have not been fighting against that point...it is rather paramount and crucial.<br>
<br>
Thank you for the spells Verant=)<br>
At least we know the big green eyes are open...:-)<br>
-Ari <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueelyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eelyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/01 10:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here it is our new enhancement</span><hr size=1> This opinion is coming from a wizard that has been playing since Beta.<br>
<br>
This spell is really a decent spell on one end of the picture.  This increases our need again to be on raids.  Many high end encounters do gate and there is no way to stop them pretty much besides all fighting on one side.  But these mobs have such high channeling that this method doesn't always work, nor is there alwasy the room.  As long as this spell doesn't have terrible resist rates and doesn't use all our mana trying to stop the mob so we can concentrate on doing damage.  Then it will be a great Raid spell.  <br>
<br>
On the other hand in a group situation, gating is rarely ever a problem.  And veteran dungeon crawlers know how to deal with gating mobs and they are usually not a problem.  Will this increase the wizard desirabilty in dungeons, ever so slightly.  And most likely with the more novice dungeon crawlers, which will probably get the wizard killed anyways.  <br>
<br>
Generally Verant still doesn't know how to seperate making wizards a COMPLETE RAID class and not a group class.  We are great at Soloing and great at Raiding.  With still the exceptions of pathetic damage output on 200k+ hp mobs.  In grouping we have fine damage output in Kunark, and low output in Velious.  This gating spell will not really help much at all in group areas.  In Multi-Group raid areas it will.  The only single group area that I can think of this will help would be Siren's Grotto and you need a really experienced group to venture there.  <br>
<br>
Overall, our raid desirability increase another good amount, while our grouping desirability increase is nil...<br>
<br>
My Guess at other possible enchancements along these lines:<br>
1. Stop mobs from Summoning<br>
2. Translocate with Hate list clear on mobs.<br>
<br>
Verant, you really need to look at the big issues that have been trailing this class since day one.  If one class constantly is saying the same thing over and over again for 2 years, which there is no other class then the wizard class that has.  Maybe you should think that we're right for once... <p><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=2 BGCOLOR=151B40>
